 century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Dive was born in 1203, in England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Sir William Dive. She had at least 1 son with Sir Hugh Bussey. She died in 1293, at the age of 90."},"et":{"1203–1293":"1203–1293","1200–1278":"1200–1278","1225–1293":"1225–1293","–Male":"Surnud","1203":"1203","1225":"1225","1278":"1278","1200":"1200","1293":"1293","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1203–1293":"1203–1293","1200–1278":"1200–1278","1225–1293":"1225–1293","–Male":"Kuollut","1203":"1203","1225":"1225","1278":"1278","1200":"1200","1293":"1293","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1203–1293":"1203–1293","1200–1278":"1200–1278","1225–1293":"1225–1293","–Male":"Décédé","1203":"1203","1225":"1225","1278":"1278","1200":"1200","1293":"1293","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Dive est née en 1203, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fille de Sir William Dive. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Sir Hugh Bussey. Elle est décédée en 1293, à l’âge de 90 ans."},"de":{"1203–1293":"1203–1293","1200–1278":"1200–1278","1225–1293":"1225–1293","–Male":"Verstorben","1203":"1203","1225":"1225","1278":"1278","1200":"1200","1293":"1293","England":"England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Dive wurde 1203 in England, United Kingdom, als Tochter von Sir William Dive geboren. Sie hatte mit Sir Hugh Bussey mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb 1293